tterson Mill || 871 || 314 || 203 || 64.6%\n|}\n\n====Magnet programs====\nThree HCPS high schools also have or are preparing for [[magnet school|magnet programs]]. Although the Science and Mathematics Academy is a separate institution, it is hosted by and shares some facilities with [[Aberdeen High School (Aberdeen, Maryland)|Aberdeen High School]], and [[Harford Technical High School]] is in itself a magnet school for academic and technical programs. [[Edgewood High School (Edgewood, Maryland)|Edgewood High School]] is in the beginning stages of the [[IB Diploma Programme|International Baccalaureate Diploma Programme]], in which the school will offer college-preparatory courses for its students, who will graduate with an internationally recognized high school diploma. Edgewood also offers the Academy of Finance program.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hcps.org/Schools/MagnetPrograms/Default.aspx|title=Harford County Public Schools Magnet Programs|website=Hcps.org|accessdate=15 April 2019}}</ref>\n\n*Academy of Finance at Edgewood High School\n*Harford Technical High School in [[Bel Air, Maryland]]\n*Homeland Security at Joppatowne High School\n*International Baccalaureate at Edgewood High School\n*Natural Resources and Agricultural Science Magnet Program at North Harford High School\n*Science and Mathematics Academy at Aberdeen High School\n\n====Mascots====\nThe school mascots are:\n*Aberdeen Eagles\n*Bel Air Bobcats\n*C. Milton Wright Mustangs\n*Edgewood Rams\n*Fallston Cougars\n*Harford Technical Cobras\n*Havre de Grace Warriors\n*Joppatowne Mariners\n*North Harford Hawks\n*Patterson Mill Huskies\n\n===Alternative/charter schools===\n*John Archer School, Bel Air,'' grades K-8''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hcps.org/Schools/Alternative/Default.aspx|title=Alternative Schools|website=Hcps.org|accessdate=15 April 2019}}</ref>\n\n==School feeder systems==\nThe images below outline the elementary and middle schools that feed students into each high school. Harford Technical is fed by students from each school, as entry is by application. The feeder system is not all-inclusive, due to magnet programs at Aberdeen, Edgewood, and Joppatowne.\n<gallery widths=105>\nImage:AberdeenFeeder.png|'''Aberdeen'''\nImage:BelAirFeeder.png|'''Bel Air'''\nImage:CMiltonFeeder.png|'''C. Milton Wright'''\nImage:EdgewoodFeeder.png|'''Edgewood'''\nImage:FallstonFeeder.png|'''Fallston'''\nImage:HDGFeeder.png|'''Havre de Grace'''\nImage:JoppaFeeder.png|'''Joppatowne'''\nImage:NHarfordFeeder.png|'''North Harford'''\nImage:PMillFeeder.png|'''Patterson Mill'''\n</gallery>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Harford Glen Environmental Education Center]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.hcps.org/ Official website]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20100615214618/http://hcps.org/aboutus/docs/minifacts.pdf Facts about HCPS]\n*[http://www.hcps.org/schools/schoolprofiles.aspx HCPS district profile]\n*[http://members.thinkport.org/ucbac Upper Chesapeake Bay Athletic Conference]\n\n{{Harford County Public Schools}}\n\n[[Category:School districts in Maryland]]\n[[Category:Education in Harford County, Maryland]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox school district\n|name                = Harford County Public Schools\n|logo                = \n|motto               = \n|type                = [[County (United States)|County]]-wide public school system\n|budget              = $450,226,984 <ref name=\"minifact\">{{cite web|url=http://www.hcps.org/aboutus/docs/minifacts.pdf|title=Facts about the Harford County Public Schools 2009-2010|accessdate=2010-02-23|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100615214618/http://hcps.org/aboutus/docs/minifacts.pdf|archivedate=2010-06-15}}</ref>\n|established         = \n|region              = [[Harford County, Maryland]]\n|grades              = Kindergarten through 12th\n|superintendent      = Dr. Sean Bulson\n|teachers            = 2827<ref name=\"minifact\" />\n|staff               = 1,500\n|students            