{"title_page": "Nihad Kre\u0161evljakovi\u0107", "text_new": "'''Nihad Kre\u0161evljakovi\u0107''' (born 24 February 1977) is a [[Bosnians|Bosnian]] historian, producer, screenwriter and director of the [[Sarajevo War Theatre]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.akta.ba/licnosti/nihad-kresevljakovic-direktor-sartr-a-borba-za-stvarne-vrijednosti/23358|title=Nihad Kre\u0161evljakovi\u0107, direktor SARTR-a: Borba za stvarne vrijednosti|publisher=akta.ba}}</ref>\n\n==Biography==\nKre\u0161evljakovi\u0107 was born in [[Sarajevo]], [[SFR Yugoslavia]]. He enrolled at the [[University of Sarajevo]], Faculty of Philosophy where he studied history. He graduated in 1999, before earning his post-graduate degree from the same institution four years later. He further studied Comparative literature. He has worked as a producer for the [[MESS (festival)|MESS International Theatre Festival]], before being named director of the festival.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://balkans.aljazeera.net/vijesti/direktor-mess-nihad-kresevljakovic-nova-teatarska-scena|title=Direktor MESS-a Nihad Kre\u0161evljakovi\u0107: Nova teatarska scena|publisher=Al Jazeera Balkans}}</ref> In 2011 he founded the Videoarhiv documentary film production company with his brother Sead.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://videoarhiv.blogger.ba/|title=About|publisher=Videoarhiv Official Website}}</ref> In 2012 he was named director of the [[Sarajevo War Theatre]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.akta.ba/licnosti/nihad-kresevljakovic-direktor-sartr-a-borba-za-stvarne-vrijednosti/23358|title=Nihad Kre\u0161evljakovi\u0107, direktor SARTR-a: Borba za stvarne vrijednosti|publisher=akta.ba}}</ref> He has worked as a screenwriter on numerous film projects. In 2019, Kre\u0161evljakovi\u0107 was awarded with the German [[KAIROS Prize]].<ref>[https://www.deutschlandfunkkultur.de/kairos-preis-fuer-bosnischen-regisseur-kresevljakovic.265.de.html?drn:news_id=1001571 Kairos-Preis f\u00fcr bosnischen Regisseur Kresevljakovic], retrieved 28 April 2019 (German)</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nHis grandfather [[Hamdija Kre\u0161evljakovi\u0107]] was a renowned Bosnian historian. His father [[Muhamed Kre\u0161evljakovi\u0107]] was the war-time mayor of Sarajevo. His twin brother Sead is a journalist, film producer and the honorary consule of [[San Marino]] in Bosnia and Herzegovina.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://balkans.aljazeera.net/profil/sead-kresevljakovic|title=Sead Kre\u0161evljakovi\u0107|publisher=Al Jazeera Balkans}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kre\u0161evljakovi\u0107, Nihad}}\n[[Category:University of Belgrade alumni]]\n[[Category:People from Sarajevo]]\n[[Category:1977 births]]\n[[Category:Bosnia and Herzegovina historians]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Bosnia and Herzegovina screenwriters]]\n", "text_old": "'''Nihad Kre\u0161evljakovi\u0107''' (born 24 February 1977) is a [[Bosnians|Bosnian]] historian, producer, screenwriter and director of the [[Sarajevo War Theatre]]. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.akta.ba/licnosti/nihad-kresevljakovic-direktor-sartr-a-borba-za-stvarne-vrijednosti/23358|title=Nihad Kre\u0161evljakovi\u0107, direktor SARTR-a: Borba za stvarne vrijednosti|publisher=akta.ba}}</ref>\n\n==Biography==\nKre\u0161evljakovi\u0107 was born in [[Sarajevo]], [[SFR Yugoslavia]]. He enrolled at the [[University of Sarajevo]], Faculty of Philosophy where he studied history. He graduated in 1999, before earning his post-graduate degree from the same institution four years later. He further studied Comparative literature. He has worked as a producer for the [[MESS (festival)|MESS International Theatre Festival]], before being named director of the festival. <ref>{{cite web|url=http://balkans.aljazeera.net/vijesti/direktor-mess-nihad-kresevljakovic-nova-teatarska-scena|title=Direktor MESS-a Nihad Kre\u0161evljakovi\u0107: Nova teatarska scena|publisher=Al Jazeera Balkans}}</ref> In 2011 he founded the Videoarhiv documentary film production company with his brother Sead. <ref>{{cite web|url=http://videoarhiv.blogger.ba/|title=About|publisher=Videoarhiv Official Website}}</ref> In 2012 he was named director of the [[Sarajevo War Theatre]]. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.akta.ba/licnosti/nihad-kresevljakovic-direktor-sartr-a-borba-za-stvarne-vrijednosti/23358|title=Nihad Kre\u0161evljakovi\u0107, direktor SARTR-a: Borba za stvarne vrijednosti|publisher=akta.ba}}</ref> He has worked as a screenwriter on numerous film projects. In 2019, Kre\u0161evljakovi\u0107 was awarded with the German [[KAIROS Prize]].<ref>[https://www.deutschlandfunkkultur.de/kairos-preis-fuer-bosnischen-regisseur-kresevljakovic.265.de.html?drn:news_id=1001571 Kairos-Preis f\u00fcr bosnischen Regisseur Kresevljakovic], retrieved 28 April 2019 (German)</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nHis grandfather [[Hamdija Kre\u0161evljakovi\u0107]] was a renowned Bosnian historian. His father [[Muhamed Kre\u0161evljakovi\u0107]] was the war-time mayor of Sarajevo. His twin brother Sead is a journalist, film producer and the honorary consule of [[San Marino]] in Bosnia and Herzegovina. <ref>{{cite web|url=http://balkans.aljazeera.net/profil/sead-kresevljakovic|title=Sead Kre\u0161evljakovi\u0107|publisher=Al Jazeera Balkans}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kre\u0161evljakovi\u0107, Nihad}}\n[[Category:University of Belgrade alumni]]\n[[Category:People from Sarajevo]]\n[[Category:1977 births]]\n[[Category:Bosnia and Herzegovina historians]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Bosnia and Herzegovina screenwriters]]\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nihad_Kre%C5%A1evljakovi%C4%87"}
